race.comment: Very plain offering after the scratchings. HARRY'S HALO (10) will make his own luck up in the leading division and gets his chance to break through. Better effort last start when lining up for the second time, battling on fairly for fourth over 1200m at Nowra. Sure to prove tough to catch. REIGN OF HONOR (5) on debut for Waterhouse/Bott will be tough to beat based on a good recent trial win at Randwick. Will take advantage of the nice gate and if he has any talent will be there at the business end. HETZENDORF (11) also resumes and can do better this time in work. New acquisition for the Michael Freedman stable after starting life with Godolphin. Firm in early markets - keep an eye on betting closer to race time. BLAZING FUTURE (4) on debut for Ryan/Alexiou has shown little at the trials but might have more to offer. Let the betting tell the story. SHERIFF'S STAR (14) made a bit of ground without threatening first-up over 1200m at Nowra. Can sneak into the top four.
